-- Migration 0055: backfill historical Stripe balance-history export
--
-- Loads a full Stripe "Balance history" CSV export for the PRIOR Stripe
-- account acct_1DF6BFAhXr9x8yiR (every exported id carries that account's
-- AhXr9x8yiR infix) into stripe_payouts + stripe_staged_charges. The live
-- API sync runs against a DIFFERENT connector account and is ongoing-only
-- (watermarked), so this historical back-catalogue can only be loaded here.
--
-- Rows: 162 payouts, 287 staged charges
-- Source: attached_assets/balance_history_1781913987279.csv
--
-- Payout rollups mirror rollupPayout() (gross = Σ charge/payment, refund =
-- Σ|refund|, fee = Σ all fees, net = gross − fee − refund); the bank-net
-- `amount` comes from each payout row's own Net. Charge date_received is the
-- charge time in America/Chicago (chargeDateReceived).
--
-- Charges are staged status='pending', match_status='unmatched', with NO
-- donor FKs: donor identity is environment-specific, so matching is left to
-- the reconciliation queue / a later matcher run in each environment. This
-- keeps the file identical + safe for dev AND prod.
--
-- SAFETY / IDEMPOTENCY:
--   * Purely additive. ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING — re-runs are a no-op and
--     any row the ongoing sync already pulled is left untouched.
--   * Payouts are inserted before charges so the stripe_payout_id FK holds.
--   * No donor / gift / intermediary FKs are written, so this does NOT depend
--     on the pending schema Publish (the stripe_* tables already exist in prod).
--
--   psql "$DATABASE_URL" -1 -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -f lib/db/migrations/0055_stripe_history_backfill.sql

ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;

ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
